# ============================================================
# GOOD FIRST ISSUE FINDER — Environment Variables
# ============================================================
# Copy this file to .env.local for local development:
#   cp .env.example .env.local
#
# NEVER commit .env.local to version control.
#
# In production (Cloudflare Workers), set secrets with:
#   wrangler secret put GITHUB_TOKEN
# ============================================================


# ------------------------------------------------------------
# GITHUB_TOKEN (REQUIRED)
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# A GitHub Personal Access Token.
# Required for: GitHub Search Issues API, GitHub Repos API
# (language/stars/forks enrichment).
#
# Without this token, the app will return 403 errors from GitHub
# and no GitHub issues will be displayed.
#
# How to create one:
#   https://github.com/settings/tokens
#   A classic token with NO scopes is sufficient for public repos.
#   Or use a fine-grained token with "Public Repositories (read-only)".
# ------------------------------------------------------------
GITHUB_TOKEN=

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# GITLAB_TOKEN (OPTIONAL)
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# A GitLab Private Token or Personal Access Token.
# Without this, requests to GitLab instances may succeed at
# reduced rate limits, or may be blocked by some instances.
#
# How to create one:
#   https://gitlab.com/-/user_settings/personal_access_tokens
#   Scope needed: read_api
#
# NOTE: This token is sent to ALL configured GitLab instances
# (gitlab.com, GNOME, Debian Salsa, KDE Invent, Freedesktop,
# Inkscape). Ensure your token is appropriate for these.
# ------------------------------------------------------------
GITLAB_TOKEN=
